# Encoder-Based PID Motor Control System

## Project Overview

This project implements a closed-loop PID motor control system using an Arduino Uno, BTS7960 motor driver, and N20 encoder motor.

The encoder continuously provides rotational feedback to the Arduino through interrupt-based pulse detection. The PID controller processes this feedback and dynamically adjusts PWM output to regulate motor behavior and reduce control error.

The project demonstrates practical implementation of embedded feedback control systems including:
- PWM motor actuation
- Encoder signal processing
- PID-based correction
- Real-time control response
- Hardware noise suppression

The system was developed and tested using real hardware components on a breadboard setup.
